using SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor;

namespace Repro;

public class MySKGLView : SKGLView
{
    private bool _customResourceAllocated = true;

    public override void Dispose()
    {
        _customResourceAllocated = false;
        Console.WriteLine("Custom dispose called");
        base.Dispose();
    }
}

proposedResponse.body:
Thanks for the suggestion! We investigated and can confirm that `SKGLView.Dispose()` is not virtual in SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor, which prevents subclasses from properly extending disposal behavior.

**Investigation:**
- Tested with SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor 2.88.9 and 3.119.2 — both have `public void Dispose()` (non-virtual)
- Attempting `override` yields `CS0506: cannot override inherited member because it is not marked virtual`
- The same pattern exists in `SKCanvasView`
- Main branch source still shows the same non-virtual Dispose

The standard .NET fix would be implementing the `Dispose(bool)` pattern ([CA1063](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/fundamentals/code-analysis/quality-rules/ca1063)).

**Workaround:** You can shadow the method with `new`, though this breaks polymorphic disposal through `IDisposable` references:

```csharp
public new void Dispose()
{
    // Custom cleanup
    base.Dispose();
}
```

We've flagged this for consideration.
